#. [character_profile]: id=Galas, race=elf, gender=male
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:18
msgid "Galas"
msgstr "Galas"

#. [character_profile]: id=Galas, race=elf, gender=male
#. [character_profile]: id=Anlindë, race=elf, gender=female
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:19 Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:50
msgid "Valley of Elynia"
msgstr "Valle de Elynia"

#. [character_profile]: id=Galas, race=elf, gender=male
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:24
msgid ""
"<b>Galas</b>, son of the late Captain Valthir, is a member of the southern "
"border patrol of the Valley of Elynia. Although born in the lush and cozy "
"forests of the inner Valley, from a very young age he took a liking to "
"accompanying his father in expeditions to safeguard the Valley from hostile "
"outsiders, learning the ins and outs of survival in the desert."
msgstr ""
"<b>Galas</b>, hijo del fallecido capitán Valthir, forma parte de la patrulla "
"fronteriza sur del Valle de Elynia. Aunque nació en los exuberantes y "
"acogedores bosques del interior del valle, desde muy pequeño le gustó "
"acompañar a su padre en expediciones para proteger el valle de extraños "
"hostiles, aprendiendo todos los secretos de la supervivencia en el desierto."

#. [additional_info]
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:28 Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:102
msgid "Alliance of the Peoples of the Far North"
msgstr "Alianza de los Pueblos del Lejano Norte"

#. [additional_info]
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:29
msgid ""
"As part of a barter to secure a new home for the forest elves in the Far "
"North, Galas pledged to join the Grand Council of the Northern Peoples, "
"along with Elynia and Mal Keshar. While doing so, he also renounced his "
"leadership of the elves, letting Lord Inodien take over his duties."
msgstr ""
"Como parte de un acuerdo para conseguir un nuevo hogar para los elfos del "
"bosque en el Lejano Norte, Galas se comprometió a unirse al Gran Consejo de "
"los Pueblos del Norte junto con Elynia y Mal Keshar. Al hacerlo, también "
"renunció a su liderazgo sobre los elfos, dejando que el señor Inodien "
"asumiera sus responsabilidades."

#. [additional_info]
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:35
msgid ""
"On the way back from Zocthanol Isle, Galas’s group was caught in a storm and "
"forced to make landfall in <b>Kalari Peninsula</b>, the location of the "
"<b>Iron Council</b> headquarters. Galas and Elynia were both captured by "
"Chaos forces during a struggle, resulting in a disastrous breakout attempt "
"where the two of them and Mal Keshar became lost in an underground "
"facility.\n"
"\n"
"While debating the best way to solve their predicament, the group was "
"ambushed by Elyssa, who emerged from the shadows and fatally struck Galas "
"from behind before anyone could react. Elynia and Mal Keshar narrowly "
"escaped via the use of teleport magic, but were ultimately unable to "
"retrieve the elf’s body."
msgstr ""
"De regreso desde la isla de Zocthanol, el grupo de Galas fue atrapado por "
"una tormenta y se vio obligado a desembarcar en la <b>península de Kalari</"
"b>, sede del cuartel general del <b>Consejo de Hierro</b>. Galas y Elynia "
"fueron capturados por fuerzas del Caos durante una lucha, lo que resultó en "
"un intento desastroso de escape en el que los tres —Galas, Elynia y Mal "
"Keshar— se perdieron en una instalación subterránea.\n"
"\n"
"Mientras discutían la mejor forma de resolver su situación, el grupo fue "
"emboscado por Elyssa, quien surgió de las sombras y golpeó fatalmente a "
"Galas por la espalda antes de que alguien pudiera reaccionar. Elynia y Mal "
"Keshar escaparon por poco usando magia de teletransportación, pero no "
"pudieron recuperar el cuerpo del elfo."

#. [character_profile]: id=Anlindë, race=elf, gender=female
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:49
msgid "Anlindë"
msgstr "Anlindë"

#. [character_profile]: id=Anlindë, race=elf, gender=female
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:57
msgid ""
"While elves normally live for approximately three hundred years, <b>Anlindë</"
"b> is a rare exception whose presence in the Valley of Elynia is rumored to "
"predate the very existence of the settlement.\n"
"\n"
"Throughout the ages, Anlindë has dedicated herself to the tedious yet "
"crucial labor of record keeping for the valley’s governing council at "
"Telchior’s Keep, thus ensuring that old elven crafts and traditions—"
"especially those pertaining to the use of faerie magic—remain alive long "
"after the Great Fall. In more recent times however, her focus has largely "
"shifted away from desk jobs into tending to the sick and wounded, putting "
"her unrivaled mastery of herbal medicine into more practical uses.\n"
"\n"
"Since Captain Valthir’s unfortunate demise, Anlindë has taken care of his "
"only son <b>Galas</b> as if he were her own, even arranging for him to be "
"personally tutored by Lord Lédinor despite his father being a complete "
"outsider to the council."
msgstr ""
"Aunque los elfos normalmente viven alrededor de trescientos años, "
"<b>Anlindë</b> es una rara excepción cuya presencia en el Valle de Elynia se "
"rumorea que es anterior a la misma existencia del asentamiento.\n"
"\n"
"A lo largo de los siglos, Anlindë se dedicó a la tediosa pero crucial tarea "
"de mantener los registros del consejo gobernante del valle en la Fortaleza "
"de Telchior, asegurando así que las antiguas artes y tradiciones élficas —"
"especialmente las relacionadas con la magia feérica— permanecieran vivas "
"mucho después de la Gran Caída. En tiempos más recientes, sin embargo, su "
"atención se ha desplazado en gran medida de los trabajos de escritorio hacia "
"el cuidado de enfermos y heridos, poniendo su incomparable dominio de la "
"medicina herbal en usos más prácticos.\n"
"\n"
"Desde la desafortunada muerte del capitán Valthir, Anlindë ha cuidado de su "
"único hijo <b>Galas</b> como si fuera suyo, incluso organizando que "
"recibiera enseñanza personal del señor Lédinor a pesar de que su padre era "
"un completo extraño para el consejo."

#. [additional_info]
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:65
msgid ""
"During the elves’ first encounter with Mal Keshar, Anlindë’s magical prowess "
"proved far greater than suspected by anyone, as a single spell—of a nature "
"unknown to even the necromancer—allowed her to weaken him enough for Galas "
"and others to finish the job. Entirely unexpected to her, however, was Galas "
"and the lich’s mutual willingness to converse civilly; and even more "
"unexpected was how this would lead to an impromptu alliance without "
"precedent in elven history."
msgstr ""
"Durante el primer encuentro de los elfos con Mal Keshar, la destreza mágica "
"de Anlindë resultó ser mucho mayor de lo que nadie sospechaba: un solo "
"hechizo —de una naturaleza desconocida incluso para el nigromante— le "
"permitió debilitarlo lo suficiente para que Galas y los demás terminaran el "
"trabajo. Sin embargo, lo que ella nunca esperó fue la disposición mutua de "
"Galas y el liche para conversar de forma civilizada; y aún más inesperado "
"fue que esto condujera a una alianza improvisada sin precedentes en la "
"historia élfica."

#. [additional_info]
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:70
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Upon meeting the <b>Lady of Light Elynia</b>, Galas, Mal Keshar, and Lady "
"Unarye learned the hidden truth behind Anlindë’s existence: she was once "
"part of the dark cult serving the <b>Demon Lord Zhangor</b> in Wesmere; "
"despite all the other priests having been executed to prevent a resurgence "
"of the wicked creature, Lord Telchior of Thelien chose to spare her life "
"alone for undisclosed reasons.\n"
"\n"
"In spite of this revelation, it was evident to all that Anlindë had "
"dedicated every instant of her continued existence to atoning for her sins "
"against elvenkind; not only that, but her advice to Lord Telchior became "
"directly responsible for the discovery of the valley which served as the "
"forest elves’ sanctuary for countless generations."
msgstr ""
"Al conocer a la <b>Dama de la Luz Elynia</b>, Galas, Mal Keshar y la dama "
"Unarye descubrieron la verdad oculta sobre la existencia de Anlindë: en el "
"pasado formó parte del culto oscuro que servía al <b>Señor Demonio Zhangor</"
"b> en Wesmere. A pesar de que todos los demás sacerdotes fueron ejecutados "
"para evitar el resurgimiento de la criatura maligna, el señor Telchior de "
"Thelien decidió perdonarle la vida únicamente a ella por razones que nunca "
"reveló.\n"
"\n"
"A pesar de esta revelación, era evidente para todos que Anlindë había "
"dedicado cada instante de su existencia continuada a expiar sus pecados "
"contra el pueblo élfico; no solo eso, sino que su consejo al señor Telchior "
"fue directamente responsable del descubrimiento del valle que sirvió como "
"refugio de los elfos del bosque durante innumerables generaciones."

#. [additional_info]
#. Keep "Chaos Warlord" gender-ambiguous if your language allows it
#. since this text will be visible in game before Elyssa's proper
#. reveal in S22A.
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:81
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"In order to buy King Asthorgar and Galas time to evacuate Herthgar before "
"the Chaos Warlord’s final siege attempt, Anlindë chose to stay behind and "
"defend the capital with the assistance of Mal Keshar’s minions and a few "
"dwarven troops. Everybody knew that it would be extremely unlikely for her "
"to survive the encounter, and indeed, she never returned from her mission. "
"Her sacrifice was not in vain, however, as it allowed the evacuation to "
"proceed mostly as planned with minimal loss of life."
msgstr ""
"Para darle tiempo al rey Asthorgar y a Galas de evacuar Herthgar antes del "
"intento final de asedio del Señor del Caos, Anlindë decidió quedarse atrás y "
"defender la capital con la ayuda de los súbditos de Mal Keshar y algunas "
"tropas enanas. Todos sabían que era extremadamente improbable que "
"sobreviviera al encuentro, y en efecto, nunca regresó de su misión. Sin "
"embargo, su sacrificio no fue en vano, ya que permitió que la evacuación se "
"llevara a cabo casi según lo planeado con pérdidas mínimas de vidas."

#. [character_profile]: id=Mal Keshar, race=undead, gender=male
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:88
msgid "Mal Keshar"
msgstr "Mal Keshar"

#. [character_profile]: id=Mal Keshar, race=undead, gender=male
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:96
msgid ""
"<b>Mal Keshar</b> — formerly <b>Malin Keshar</b> — is an ancient Lich from "
"the times before the Fall, hailing from the old human kingdom known as "
"<b>Wesnoth</b>.\n"
"\n"
"His origins can be traced back to the border town of Parthyn, at the time "
"afflicted by constant orcish incursions. The timely intervention of a "
"necromancer known as <b>Darken Volk</b> during a battle which cost Parthyn "
"many lives, including that of Malin Keshar’s father, prompted the young boy "
"to begin his travels and apprenticeship under the dark mage. While his "
"master’s fate has been lost to history, what is known is that Malin Keshar "
"attained lichdom and became the bane of the orcish tribes for a thousand "
"years."
msgstr ""
"<b>Mal Keshar</b> —antes <b>Malin Keshar</b>— es un antiguo liche de la "
"época anterior a la Caída, originario del viejo reino humano conocido como "
"<b>Wesnoth</b>.\n"
"\n"
"Su origen se remonta al pueblo fronterizo de Parthyn, que en ese entonces "
"sufría constantes incursiones orcas. La intervención oportuna de un "
"nigromante conocido como <b>Darken Volk</b> durante una batalla que costó "
"muchas vidas en Parthyn, incluida la del padre de Malin Keshar, impulsó al "
"joven a comenzar sus viajes y aprendizaje bajo el mago oscuro. Aunque el "
"destino de su maestro se ha perdido en la historia, se sabe que Malin Keshar "
"alcanzó el estado de liche y se convirtió en la pesadilla de las tribus "
"orcas durante mil años."

#. [additional_info]
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:103
msgid ""
"As part of Galas’s barter to secure a new home for the forest elves in the "
"Far North, Mal Keshar pledged allegiance to the <b>Grand Council of the "
"Northern Peoples</b>."
msgstr ""
"Como parte del acuerdo de Galas para asegurar un nuevo hogar para los elfos "
"del bosque en el Lejano Norte, Mal Keshar juró lealtad al <b>Gran Consejo de "
"los Pueblos del Norte</b>."

#. [additional_info]
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:108
msgid ""
"Mal Keshar proved a decisive factor in overcoming the obstacles Galas’s "
"group encountered on their way to the lair of the <b>Chaos Emperor</b> in "
"Inferno. Unfortunately, the severe amount of damage he sustained from "
"fighting Elyssa, Argan, and Elynia in quick succession caused his power to "
"wane considerably. Despite this, Mal Keshar continued to be a force to be "
"reckoned with, rivaling even the most powerful priests and necromancers at "
"Uria’s service."
msgstr ""
"Mal Keshar resultó ser un factor decisivo para superar los obstáculos que el "
"grupo de Galas encontró en su camino hacia la guarida del <b>Emperador del "
"Caos</b> en Inferno. Desafortunadamente, el grave daño que sufrió al "
"enfrentarse consecutivamente a Elyssa, Argan y Elynia hizo que su poder "
"disminuyera considerablemente. A pesar de ello, Mal Keshar siguió siendo una "
"fuerza temida, rivalizando incluso con los sacerdotes y nigromantes más "
"poderosos al servicio de Uria."

#. [additional_info]
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:115
msgid ""
"At the end of the group’s confrontation with the empowered <b>Shaxthal "
"Queen</b> at the Wesmere Hive’s Abaddon facility, Mal Keshar and all his "
"undead minions were caught in the massive whirlpool of energy released from "
"the beast’s shattered core, causing his soul to be forcibly released from "
"his body. Only minutes after, the entire facility along with the ruined "
"plains of Wesmere completely vanished off the face of Irdya."
msgstr ""
"Al final del enfrentamiento del grupo contra la fortalecida <b>Reina "
"Shaxthal</b> en la instalación Abaddon del Enjambre de Wesmere, Mal Keshar y "
"todos sus súbditos no muertos fueron atrapados en el enorme remolino de "
"energía liberado del núcleo destrozado de la bestia, lo que provocó que su "
"alma fuera arrancada forzosamente de su cuerpo. Solo minutos después, toda "
"la instalación junto con las llanuras arruinadas de Wesmere desaparecieron "
"por completo de la superficie de Irdya."

#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:121
msgid ""
"Following their participation in the War of Wesmere, Elynia and Argan "
"descended into the deepest reaches the Heart Mountains seeking answers "
"regarding the Demon Lord and his place of origin. Tragically, an earthquake "
"caused the earth to claim Argan’s life, not even leaving a body for Elynia "
"to retrieve. Stricken with grief, the faerie requested the assistance of "
"dwarves to seal her in a custom-built burial chamber, intending to lay "
"dormant until the day Irdya would recover from complete devastation."
msgstr ""
"Tras su participación en la Guerra de Wesmere, Elynia y Argan descendieron a "
"las profundidades de las Montañas Profundas en busca de respuestas sobre el "
"Señor Demonio y su lugar de origen. Trágicamente, un terremoto hizo que la "
"tierra reclamara la vida de Argan, sin dejar siquiera un cuerpo para que "
"Elynia pudiera recuperarlo. Abrumada por el dolor, la feérica pidió ayuda a "
"los enanos para sellarla en una cámara funeraria construida especialmente "
"para ella, con la intención de permanecer dormida hasta el día en que Irdya "
"se recuperara de la devastación total."

#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:125
msgid ""
"Galas’s band confronted Argan in his own lair in the frozen wastes of "
"Inferno, initially finding themselves completely outclassed by the sorcerer. "
"However, Elynia’s ingenuity allowed her to fight him on equal ground by "
"channeling the Power of the Union straight from him at close quarters. "
"Despite <b>Uria</b> attempting to turn the tide by mutating and puppeteering "
"Argan’s body, Elynia managed to subdue him with Galas and Mal Keshar’s help. "
"Unable to find an alternative solution to her quandary, she struck at his "
"heart with the full extent of her own power, thus putting an end to his "
"sinister reign over Irdya."
msgstr ""
"La banda de Galas enfrentó a Argan en su propia guarida en los yermos "
"helados de Inferno, encontrándose inicialmente completamente superados por "
"el hechicero. Sin embargo, la ingeniosidad de Elynia le permitió luchar en "
"igualdad de condiciones canalizando el Poder de la Unión directamente desde "
"él a corta distancia. A pesar de que <b>Uria</b> intentó cambiar el rumbo "
"mutando y manipulando el cuerpo de Argan como marioneta, Elynia logró "
"someterlo con la ayuda de Galas y Mal Keshar. Sin encontrar otra solución a "
"su dilema, golpeó su corazón con toda la extensión de su propio poder, "
"poniendo así fin a su siniestro reinado sobre Irdya."

#. [character_profile]: id=Elynia, race=faerie, gender=female
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:130
msgid "Elynia, the Lady of Light"
msgstr "Elynia, la Dama de la Luz"

#. [character_profile]: id=Elynia, race=faerie, gender=female
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:136
msgid "Source of Light, Protector of the Elves of Irdya"
msgstr "Fuente de Luz, Protectora de los Elfos de Irdya"

#. [character_profile]: id=Elynia, race=faerie, gender=female
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:137
msgid "Ka’lian of Wesmere (before the Fall)"
msgstr "Ka’lian de Wesmere (antes de la Caída)"

#. [character_profile]: id=Elynia, race=faerie, gender=female
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:147
msgid ""
"Better known by elves and humans as the <b>Lady of Light</b> throughout "
"history before the Fall, <b>Elynia</b> is one of the two heroes that once "
"wielded the Union of Light and Darkness against Irdya’s greatest foe, the "
"<b>Demon Lord Zhangor</b>.\n"
"\n"
"Although very few records remain of her past life amongst elvenkind, it is "
"believed that she was raised in the great woods of Wesmere by an enchantress "
"who had close ties with the old Ka’lian. Having attained a seemingly eternal "
"lifespan through her mastery of Light, Elynia once made a name for herself "
"by achieving many feats as a wandering peace-keeper traveling all across the "
"Great Continent. Although the civilizations of the Golden Era are long gone, "
"a few hazy legends resulting from her participation in past events still "
"linger in the public consciousness."
msgstr ""
"Conocida por elfos y humanos como la <b>Dama de la Luz</b> a lo largo de la "
"historia anterior a la Caída, <b>Elynia</b> es una de las dos heroínas que "
"en su momento empuñaron la Unión de Luz y Oscuridad contra el mayor enemigo "
"de Irdya, el <b>Señor Demonio Zhangor</b>.\n"
"\n"
"Aunque quedan muy pocos registros de su vida pasada entre los elfos, se cree "
"que fue criada en los grandes bosques de Wesmere por una encantadora que "
"tenía estrechos lazos con el antiguo Ka’lian. Habiendo alcanzado una "
"longevidad aparentemente eterna gracias a su dominio de la Luz, Elynia se "
"hizo famosa por realizar numerosas hazañas como pacificadora errante que "
"viajaba por todo el Gran Continente. Aunque las civilizaciones de la Era "
"Dorada desaparecieron hace mucho, algunas leyendas difusas derivadas de su "
"participación en eventos pasados aún perduran en la conciencia pública."

#. [additional_info]
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:155
msgid ""
"Alliance of the Peoples of the Far North, Ka’lian of Wesmere (before the "
"Fall)"
msgstr ""
"Alianza de los Pueblos del Lejano Norte, Ka’lian de Wesmere (antes de la "
"Caída)"

#. [additional_info]
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:156
msgid ""
"As part of Galas’s barter to secure a new home for the forest elves in the "
"Far North, Elynia pledged allegiance to the <b>Grand Council of the Northern "
"Peoples</b>."
msgstr ""
"Como parte del acuerdo de Galas para asegurar un nuevo hogar para los elfos "
"del bosque en el Lejano Norte, Elynia juró lealtad al <b>Gran Consejo de los "
"Pueblos del Norte</b>."

#. [additional_info]
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:161
msgid ""
"Owing to twisted machinations of fate, Elynia’s partner <b>Argan</b>—once "
"known as the <b>Master of Darkness</b> and co-wielder of the Union of Light "
"and Darkness—became Uria’s most valued vassal and took upon the title of "
"<b>Chaos Emperor</b>."
msgstr ""
"Debido a las retorcidas maquinaciones del destino, la pareja de Elynia, "
"<b>Argan</b> —antes conocido como el <b>Maestro de la Oscuridad</b> y co-"
"portador de la Unión de Luz y Oscuridad— se convirtió en el vasallo más "
"valioso de Uria y asumió el título de <b>Emperador del Caos</b>."

#. [additional_info]
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:169
msgid "Source of Light, Protector of the Elves of Irdya, Eloh"
msgstr "Fuente de Luz, Protectora de los Elfos de Irdya, Eloh"

#. [additional_info]
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:176
msgid ""
"Alliance of the Peoples of the Far North (formerly), Ka’lian of Wesmere "
"(before the Fall)"
msgstr ""
"Alianza de los Pueblos del Lejano Norte (anteriormente), Ka’lian de Wesmere "
"(antes de la Caída)"

#. [additional_info]
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:181
msgid ""
"Sent by the <b>Demon Lord Ergea</b> in search of a “power hidden beneath "
"Kalari”, Elynia confronted the <b>Chaos Warlord Elyssa</b> in an abandoned "
"underground section of the stronghold. This time, the demoness made no "
"secret of her possession of Yechnagoth’s legacy as the <b>Guardian of "
"Darkness</b>, and promptly killed Elynia in combat."
msgstr ""
"Enviada por el <b>Señor Demonio Ergea</b> en busca de un «poder oculto bajo "
"Kalari», Elynia enfrentó a la <b>Señora de la Guerra del Caos Elyssa</b> en "
"una sección subterránea abandonada de la fortaleza. Esta vez, la demonio no "
"ocultó su posesión del legado de Yechnagoth como la <b>Guardiana de la "
"Oscuridad</b>, y mató rápidamente a Elynia en combate."

#. [additional_info]
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:186
msgid "Elynia, the Guardian of Earth"
msgstr "Elynia, la Guardiana de la Tierra"

#. [additional_info]
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:187
msgid "Lady of Light, Source of Light, Protector of the Elves of Irdya, Eloh"
msgstr "Dama de la Luz, Fuente de Luz, Protectora de los Elfos de Irdya, Eloh"

#. [additional_info]
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:188
msgid "The Ten Guardians"
msgstr "Los Diez Guardianes"

#. [additional_info]
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:189
msgid ""
"Some time after, Elynia came back to life as the <b>Guardian of Earth</b> on "
"Irdya. Despite her godlike potential, she has been unable to make proper use "
"of her power due to a complete lack of understanding of her situation—her "
"<i>curse</i>—coupled with an intense pain beyond description."
msgstr ""
"Algún tiempo después, Elynia resucitó como la <b>Guardiana de la Tierra</b> "
"en Irdya. A pesar de su potencial divino, no ha podido hacer un uso adecuado "
"de su poder debido a una completa falta de comprensión de su situación —su "
"<i>maldición</i>— combinada con un dolor intenso más allá de toda "
"descripción."

#. [character_profile]: id=Elyssa, race=shaxthal, gender=female
#. Keep "Chaos Warlord" gender-ambiguous if your language allows it.
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:197
msgid "female^Chaos Warlord"
msgstr "Señora de la Guerra del Caos"

#. [character_profile]: id=Elyssa, race=shaxthal, gender=female
#. [character_profile]: id=Uria, race=demon, gender=female
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:203 Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:291
msgid "Chaos Empire"
msgstr "Imperio del Caos"

#. [character_profile]: id=Elyssa, race=shaxthal, gender=female
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:214
msgid ""
"Evidence suggests that this seemingly half-machine, half-human creature "
"serves as the Chaos Emperor’s right hand, enforcing his will and instilling "
"fear and respect into his enemies and servants alike even in his absence."
msgstr ""
"Las evidencias sugieren que esta criatura aparentemente mitad máquina, mitad "
"humana sirve como la mano derecha del Emperador del Caos, imponiendo su "
"voluntad e infundiendo miedo y respeto tanto a sus enemigos como a sus "
"sirvientes, incluso en su ausencia."

#. [additional_info]
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:218
msgid "Elyssa, the Chaos Warlord"
msgstr "Elyssa, la Señora de la Guerra del Caos"

#. [additional_info]
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:219
msgid "Fire of Uria"
msgstr "Fuego de Uria"

#. [additional_info]
#. [additional_info]: race=shaxthal
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:220 Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:267
msgid "Chaos Empire’s Iron Council"
msgstr "Consejo de Hierro del Imperio del Caos"

#. [additional_info]
#. Keep "Chaos Warlord" gender-ambiguous if your language allows it.
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:227
msgid ""
"Following her defeat at the hands of the Lady of Light and Mal Keshar, the "
"Chaos Warlord revealed herself to be <b>Elyssa</b>, a former scholar who "
"dedicated her life to studying the ancient Wesnoth Empire’s history. "
"Additional information from the dwarves of Herthgar indicates that a Red "
"Mage matching her description once journeyed alongside Kalehssar’s people "
"and spent time with the dwarves of Gnalvarden before disappearing back into "
"the sands. It is currently unknown what events resulted in her "
"transformation into the monstrous biomechanical demon she is now.\n"
"\n"
"Following Anlindë's self-sacrifice in the capital of Herthgar, Elyssa "
"confronted the heroes in the lower levels of the Heart and nearly won, were "
"it not for Elynia’s use Light magic to temporarily blind her in order to "
"escape and regroup. Although Elyssa eventually found the band again, by then "
"Elynia and Mal Keshar had figured out how to channel the Darkness magic "
"radiating from the Chaos fortress in order to empower themselves with the "
"Union of Light and Darkness. After forcing Elyssa to retreat and regroup "
"multiple times, the duo managed to defeat the demoness in direct combat, but "
"Elynia chose at the last moment to spare her life rather than execute her."
msgstr ""
"Tras su derrota a manos de la Dama de la Luz y Mal Keshar, la Señora de la "
"Guerra del Caos se reveló como <b>Elyssa</b>, una antigua erudita que dedicó "
"su vida a estudiar la historia del antiguo Imperio de Wesnoth. Información "
"adicional de los enanos de Herthgar indica que una Maga Roja que coincidía "
"con su descripción viajó alguna vez junto al pueblo de Kalehssar y pasó "
"tiempo con los enanos de Gnalvarden antes de desaparecer nuevamente en las "
"arenas. Actualmente se desconoce qué eventos resultaron en su transformación "
"en la monstruosa demonio biomecánica que es ahora.\n"
"\n"
"Tras el autosacrificio de Anlindë en la capital de Herthgar, Elyssa enfrentó "
"a los héroes en los niveles inferiores del Corazón y casi ganó, de no ser "
"por el uso que Elynia hizo de la magia de Luz para cegarla temporalmente y "
"poder escapar y reagruparse. Aunque Elyssa eventualmente encontró de nuevo a "
"la banda, para entonces Elynia y Mal Keshar ya habían descubierto cómo "
"canalizar la magia de Oscuridad que emanaba de la fortaleza del Caos para "
"empoderarse con la Unión de Luz y Oscuridad. Tras obligar a Elyssa a "
"retirarse y reagruparse varias veces, el dúo logró derrotarla en combate "
"directo, pero Elynia decidió en el último momento perdonarle la vida en "
"lugar de ejecutarla."

#. [additional_info]
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:235
msgid "Guardian of Darkness, Fire of Uria"
msgstr "Guardiana de la Oscuridad, Fuego de Uria"

#. [additional_info]
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:240
msgid "Elyssa, the Guardian of Darkness"
msgstr "Elyssa, la Guardiana de la Oscuridad"

#. [additional_info]
#. Keep "Chaos Warlord" gender-ambiguous if your language allows it.
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:242
msgid "Chaos Warlord, Fire of Uria"
msgstr "Señora de la Guerra del Caos, Fuego de Uria"

#. [additional_info]
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:243
msgid "Chaos Empire’s Iron Council (formerly)"
msgstr "Consejo de Hierro del Imperio del Caos (anteriormente)"

#. [character_profile]: id=Argan, race=human, gender=male
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:250
msgid "Argan, the Master of Darkness"
msgstr "Argan, el Amo de la Oscuridad"

#. [character_profile]: id=Argan, race=human, gender=male
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:257
msgid ""
"Better known by elves and humans as the <b>Master of Darkness</b> throughout "
"history before the Fall, <b>Argan</b> is one of the two heroes that once "
"wielded the Union of Light and Darkness against Irdya’s greatest foe, the "
"<b>Demon Lord Zhangor</b>.\n"
"\n"
"Very few records exist of Argan’s past life, and absolutely none of his "
"story before first encountering <b>Elynia</b>, the one who would eventually "
"become his lover and co-wielder of the Union. Past elven scholars would even "
"dare suggest that he was not really from the Great Continent, owing to his "
"sudden appearance and lack of knowledge about the world at the time."
msgstr ""
"Conocido por elfos y humanos como el <b>Maestro de la Oscuridad</b> a lo "
"largo de la historia anterior a la Caída, <b>Argan</b> es uno de los dos "
"héroes que en su momento empuñaron la Unión de Luz y Oscuridad contra el "
"mayor enemigo de Irdya, el <b>Señor Demonio Zhangor</b>.\n"
"\n"
"Existen muy pocos registros de la vida pasada de Argan, y absolutamente "
"ninguno de su historia antes de encontrarse por primera vez con <b>Elynia</"
"b>, quien eventualmente se convertiría en su amante y co-portadora de la "
"Unión. Antiguos eruditos élficos incluso se atrevieron a sugerir que no era "
"realmente del Gran Continente, debido a su aparición repentina y su falta de "
"conocimiento sobre el mundo en ese momento."

#. [additional_info]: race=shaxthal
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:265
msgid "Argan, the Chaos Emperor"
msgstr "Argan, el Emperador del Caos"

#. [additional_info]: race=shaxthal
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:266
msgid "Master of Darkness, Voice of Uria, Mal-Zagarn"
msgstr "Maestro de la Oscuridad, Voz de Uria, Mal-Zagarn"

#. [additional_info]: race=shaxthal
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:276
msgid ""
"Owing to twisted machinations of fate, Argan became Uria’s most valued "
"vassal and took upon the title of <b>Chaos Emperor</b> in this era on "
"Irdya.\n"
"\n"
"Following his accident in the Heart Mountains, Argan was somehow found by "
"Uria and reshaped into a humanoid biomechanical creature wielding a fragment "
"of her power, becoming her anointed Voice on Irdya. Aided by the power of "
"demons from Inferno, he united the peoples of the Great Desert and various "
"coastal regions into one Chaos Empire, with the ultimate aim of subduing and "
"encompassing all of Irdya."
msgstr ""
"Debido a las retorcidas maquinaciones del destino, Argan se convirtió en el "
"vasallo más valioso de Uria y asumió el título de <b>Emperador del Caos</b> "
"en esta era en Irdya.\n"
"\n"
"Tras su accidente en las Montañas Profundas, Argan fue encontrado de alguna "
"manera por Uria y transformado en una criatura biomecánica humanoide que "
"empuñaba un fragmento de su poder, convirtiéndose en su Voz ungida en Irdya. "
"Ayudado por el poder de los demonios de Inferno, unió a los pueblos del Gran "
"Desierto y varias regiones costeras en un solo Imperio del Caos, con el "
"objetivo final de someter y abarcar toda Irdya."

#. [character_profile]: id=Uria, race=demon, gender=female
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:286
msgid "Uria"
msgstr "Uria"

#. [character_profile]: id=Uria, race=demon, gender=female
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:290
msgid "Mother of All Demons"
msgstr "Madre de Todos los Demonios"

#. [character_profile]: id=Uria, race=demon, gender=female
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:294
msgid ""
"The soldiers and demons at the Chaos Empire’s service mention <b>Uria</b> "
"very often, referring to her as an unforgiving yet highly-respected goddess. "
"Past records do seldom mention one such Uria, claimed to be the <b>Mother of "
"All Demons</b>, the creator of all monsters who were once relegated to "
"<b>Inferno</b>."
msgstr ""
"Los soldados y demonios al servicio del Imperio del Caos mencionan muy a "
"menudo a <b>Uria</b>, refiriéndose a ella como una diosa implacable pero muy "
"respetada. Los registros antiguos rara vez mencionan a una tal Uria, "
"considerada la <b>Madre de Todos los Demonios</b>, la creadora de todos los "
"monstruos que alguna vez fueron relegados a <b>Inferno</b>."

#. [additional_info]
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:298
msgid "Uria, the Guardian of Life"
msgstr "Uria, la Guardiana de la Vida"

#. [additional_info]
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:299
msgid "Mother of All Demons, Goddess of Life, Mistress of the Void"
msgstr "Madre de Todos los Demonios, Diosa de la Vida, Señora del Vacío"

#. [additional_info]
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:300
msgid "The Ten Guardians, Chaos Empire"
msgstr "Los Diez Guardianes, Imperio del Caos"

#. [additional_info]
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:301
msgid ""
"It turns out that Uria is not only real, but also unlike Yechnagoth she is "
"very much alive and active within her domain. She is occasionally identified "
"as the <b>Guardian of Life</b>, one of ten powerful demons of old with "
"godlike powers over the different aspects of the universe.\n"
"\n"
"The late <b>Chaos Emperor Argan</b> served as her <b>Voice</b>, her emissary "
"and highest authority on Irdya; the one in charge of communicating her will "
"to the <b>Iron Triad</b> and the Lorekeepers of the Empire.\n"
"\n"
"Upon realizing that Argan might not win the fight against Galas’s group on "
"his own, Uria attempted to turn the tide by mutating and puppeteering his "
"body."
msgstr ""
"Resulta que Uria no solo es real, sino que, a diferencia de Yechnagoth, está "
"muy viva y activa dentro de su dominio. En ocasiones se la identifica como "
"la <b>Guardiana de la Vida</b>, una de las diez poderosas demonios antiguos "
"con poderes divinos sobre los diferentes aspectos del universo.\n"
"\n"
"El fallecido <b>Emperador del Caos Argan</b> sirvió como su <b>Voz</b>, su "
"emisario y máxima autoridad en Irdya; el encargado de comunicar su voluntad "
"al <b>Tríada de Hierro</b> y a los Guardianes del Saber del Imperio.\n"
"\n"
"Al darse cuenta de que Argan podría no ganar la lucha contra el grupo de "
"Galas por sí solo, Uria intentó cambiar el rumbo mutando y manipulando su "
"cuerpo como marioneta."

#. [additional_info]
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:310
msgid ""
"She subsequently attempted the same tactic by turning <b>Lédinor</b> into a "
"thrall during the group’s escape from the collapsing capital."
msgstr ""
"Posteriormente intentó la misma táctica convirtiendo a <b>Lédinor</b> en un "
"esclavo durante la huida del grupo de la capital colapsante."

#. [story_recap]: id=UtBS
#: Naia/journey/recap.cfg:5
msgid "Under the Burning Suns"
msgstr "Bajo los soles ardientes"

#. [story_recap]: id=UtBS
#: Naia/journey/recap.cfg:6
msgid ""
"One fateful night, the young <b>Kalehssar</b> of the <b>Quenoth elves</b> "
"hears the voice of the goddess <b>Eloh</b> in his sleep, warning him of a "
"great disaster that will require him to lead his people out of the desert "
"under her guidance. He is then abruptly woken up by utter pandemonium as "
"rocks rain from the sky, laying waste to the elves’ home in the desert and "
"ending many lives.\n"
"\n"
"With Kaleh turning out to be the closest surviving relative of their late "
"leader Tanuil, and necromancers and other barbarians threatening to take "
"advantage of the chaos and finish them off, the desert elves rally under his "
"command and accept his instruction to lead an exodus across the sands in "
"search of a new home.\n"
"\n"
"After a long and treacherous journey through the desert, the Quenoth elves "
"arrive at a mountain range. Kaleh has once again been visited by their "
"goddess in his dreams and been advised to lead his people underground to get "
"past the mountains. Despite some initial reluctance, the elves descend into "
"the depths, braving many obstacles along the way but also making new "
"steadfast allies in the darkness.\n"
"\n"
"As he and his people finally reach the surface, Kaleh is visited by the "
"goddess again; this time she manifests not in his dreams, but while he is "
"wide awake in the physical realm. The encounter quickly turns sour once Eloh "
"notices that the elf has not only opted not to exterminate the denizens of "
"the underground like she planned, but even gone as far as to befriend them. "
"The leader of a troop of humans arrives and suspects the Quenoth elves of "
"slaughtering his kinsmen despite them arriving to the surface after the "
"fact. When the human announces his decision to bring the elves to the "
"<b>Iron Council</b> for judgment, Eloh commands Kaleh to submit to their "
"will; sensing something amiss, Kaleh refuses, earning him the scorn of Eloh "
"and the humans both, and igniting an armed confrontation with the latter as "
"the goddess vanishes.\n"
"\n"
"Some time after the elves have successfully repelled the human soldiers, a "
"scouting party returns with a bizarre aquatic creature communicating his "
"leader’s desire to speak in person with Kaleh. Soon, the elves learn that "
"the creature is a merman, and an emissary of the high priestess of his "
"people. As the merfok appear to know crucial information about Kaleh’s "
"predicament, he agrees to help the merman rescue his brethren, who are being "
"held captive for ritual sacrifice by the humans.\n"
"\n"
"Soon, the elves successfully infiltrate the Iron Council’s coastal "
"settlement in Ygriz, managing to rescue some of the merfolk so that they can "
"guide them to their high priestess. Before they can do so, however, Eloh "
"makes a new appearance, this time visible to everyone; she reveals Kaleh’s "
"disobedience and betrayal to all, and successfully turns many of his "
"compatriots against him. In order to quell the ensuing dispute and avoid "
"further bloodshed, Kaleh sneaks past the rebels’ forces and destroys the "
"physical avatar of Eloh, declaring her a mere impostor intent on sowing "
"discord amongst the elves to accelerate their destruction.\n"
"\n"
"Kaleh’s people commandeer some of the ships at the Iron Council’s "
"headquarters and sail off the Great Continent into the open ocean, where "
"they finally meet the high priestess <b>Melusand</b> of the merfolk. The "
"mermaid reveals the truth behind the impostor: she turns out to be a dark "
"goddess able to corrupt and control the minds of creatures, with faerie "
"beings such as elves and merfolk being the most naturally resistant to her "
"influence; her name is <b>Yechnagoth, the Eater of Souls</b>.\n"
"\n"
"Well aware that the goddess already has set her sights on them and "
"confrontation is inevitable no matter where they go next, Kaleh and his "
"friends decide to lead an all-out assault on Yechnagoth’s residence in "
"<b>Zocthanol Isle</b> with the merfolk’s assistance. Once they take most of "
"her defensive forces down, the false Eloh makes a new appearance and invites "
"Kaleh to join her for a personal audience at her citadel. Despite his "
"friends’ protests, he acquiesces and heads into Eloh’s sanctum alone; this "
"does not stop them from secretly following him, however.\n"
"\n"
"Inside Yechnagoth’s lair, Kaleh’s friends find him seemingly unconscious on "
"the ground, while the goddess shows them how she is able to brainwash even "
"elves now that they are all gathered in her own dominion. Kaleh stands up "
"and seemingly obeys Yechnagoth’s command, only to stab her in an act of "
"defiance the moment he is close enough to her. After a brief confrontation "
"with the brainwashed elves, the enraged goddess reveals her true form, that "
"of a colossal, twisted, dark abomination with no discernible body features "
"other than veins brimming with teal blood. Despite facing a creature unlike "
"anything they had ever seen before, Kaleh and his group prevail against her "
"and her progeny, destroying her and releasing her armies from her control; "
"thus the Eater of Souls’ brief reign on Irdya comes to an end.\n"
"\n"
"The Quenoth elves proceed to clean up the now-abandoned island, renaming it "
"<b>Quenoth Isle</b>, and adopting it as their new permanent home."
msgstr ""
"Una noche fatídica, el joven <b>Kalehssar</b> de los <b>elfos de Quenoth</b> "
"escucha en sueños la voz de la diosa <b>Eloh</b>, advirtiéndole de una gran "
"catástrofe que lo obligará a guiar a su pueblo fuera del desierto bajo su "
"dirección. De pronto es despertado por un caos absoluto cuando rocas caen "
"del cielo, destruyendo el hogar de los elfos en el desierto y acabando con "
"muchas vidas.\n"
"\n"
"Al resultar ser Kaleh el pariente vivo más cercano de su difunto líder "
"Tanuil, y con nigromantes y otros bárbaros amenazando con aprovechar el caos "
"para acabar con ellos, los elfos del desierto se reúnen bajo su mando y "
"aceptan su instrucción de liderar un éxodo a través de las arenas en busca "
"de un nuevo hogar.\n"
"\n"
"Tras un largo y traicionero viaje por el desierto, los elfos de Quenoth "
"llegan a una cadena montañosa. Kaleh ha sido visitado nuevamente por su "
"diosa en sueños y se le ha aconsejado guiar a su pueblo bajo tierra para "
"atravesar las montañas. A pesar de cierta reticencia inicial, los elfos "
"descienden a las profundidades, enfrentando muchos obstáculos pero también "
"ganando nuevos aliados firmes en la oscuridad.\n"
"\n"
"Cuando finalmente alcanzan la superficie, Kaleh es visitado de nuevo por la "
"diosa; esta vez se manifiesta no en sueños, sino estando él completamente "
"despierto en el mundo físico. El encuentro se torna rápidamente amargo "
"cuando Eloh nota que el elfo no solo decidió no exterminar a los habitantes "
"del subsuelo como ella había planeado, sino que incluso llegó a hacerse "
"amigo de ellos. El líder de una tropa humana llega y sospecha que los elfos "
"de Quenoth masacraron a sus compatriotas a pesar de haber llegado a la "
"superficie después del hecho. Cuando el humano anuncia su decisión de llevar "
"a los elfos ante el <b>Consejo de Hierro</b> para ser juzgados, Eloh ordena "
"a Kaleh someterse a su voluntad; al percibir algo extraño, Kaleh se niega, "
"ganándose el desprecio tanto de Eloh como de los humanos, e iniciando un "
"enfrentamiento armado con estos últimos mientras la diosa desaparece.\n"
"\n"
"Algún tiempo después de que los elfos repelieran con éxito a los soldados "
"humanos, un grupo de exploración regresa con una extraña criatura acuática "
"que comunica el deseo de su líder de hablar en persona con Kaleh. Pronto, "
"los elfos descubren que la criatura es un sirénido y emisario de la suma "
"sacerdotisa de su pueblo. Como los sirénidos parecen poseer información "
"crucial sobre la situación de Kaleh, él acepta ayudar al sirénido a rescatar "
"a sus hermanos, que están siendo retenidos cautivos para un sacrificio "
"ritual por los humanos.\n"
"\n"
"Pronto, los elfos logran infiltrarse con éxito en el asentamiento costero "
"del Consejo de Hierro en Ygriz, rescatando a algunos sirénidos para que los "
"guíen hasta su suma sacerdotisa. Sin embargo, antes de poder hacerlo, Eloh "
"hace una nueva aparición, esta vez visible para todos; revela la "
"desobediencia y traición de Kaleh a todos y logra volver a muchos de sus "
"compatriotas en su contra. Para calmar la disputa y evitar más derramamiento "
"de sangre, Kaleh se infiltra entre las fuerzas rebeldes y destruye el avatar "
"físico de Eloh, declarándola una mera impostora que buscaba sembrar "
"discordia entre los elfos para acelerar su destrucción.\n"
"\n"
"El pueblo de Kaleh se apodera de algunos barcos en el cuartel general del "
"Consejo de Hierro y navega lejos del Gran Continente hacia el océano "
"abierto, donde finalmente se encuentran con la suma sacerdotisa <b>Melusand</"
"b> de los sirénidos. La sirena revela la verdad detrás de la impostora: "
"resulta ser una diosa oscura capaz de corromper y controlar las mentes de "
"las criaturas, siendo los seres feéricos como elfos y sirénidos los más "
"naturalmente resistentes a su influencia; su nombre es <b>Yechnagoth, la "
"Devoradora de Almas</b>.\n"
"\n"
"Conscientes de que la diosa ya los tiene en la mira y que el enfrentamiento "
"es inevitable sin importar a dónde vayan, Kaleh y sus amigos deciden liderar "
"un asalto total contra la residencia de Yechnagoth en la <b>isla de "
"Zocthanol</b> con la ayuda de los sirénidos. Una vez que derriban la mayoría "
"de sus fuerzas defensivas, la falsa Eloh hace una nueva aparición e invita a "
"Kaleh a una audiencia personal en su ciudadela. A pesar de las protestas de "
"sus amigos, él acepta y se dirige solo al santuario de Eloh; sin embargo, "
"esto no impide que ellos lo sigan en secreto.\n"
"\n"
"Dentro de la guarida de Yechnagoth, los amigos de Kaleh lo encuentran "
"aparentemente inconsciente en el suelo, mientras la diosa les muestra cómo "
"ahora es capaz de lavar el cerebro incluso a los elfos al estar todos "
"reunidos en su propio dominio. Kaleh se pone de pie y aparentemente obedece "
"la orden de Yechnagoth, solo para apuñalarla en un acto de desafío en el "
"momento en que está lo suficientemente cerca. Tras un breve enfrentamiento "
"con los elfos lavados de cerebro, la diosa enfurecida revela su verdadera "
"forma: la de una abominación oscura colosal y retorcida sin rasgos "
"corporales discernibles más que venas llenas de sangre verdeazulada. A pesar "
"de enfrentarse a una criatura como ninguna que hubieran visto antes, Kaleh y "
"su grupo prevalecen contra ella y su progenie, destruyéndola y liberando a "
"sus ejércitos de su control; así termina el breve reinado de la Devoradora "
"de Almas en Irdya.\n"
"\n"
"Los elfos de Quenoth proceden a limpiar la isla ahora abandonada, "
"renombrándola <b>isla de Quenoth</b> y adoptándola como su nuevo hogar "
"permanente."

#. [world_entry]: id=Irdya
#: Naia/journey/world.cfg:5
msgid "Irdya"
msgstr "Irdya"

#. [world_entry]: id=Irdya
#: Naia/journey/world.cfg:6
msgid ""
"<b>Irdya</b> is the name of this vast world. It has existed since time "
"immemorial and gone through countless changes, the latest of which is a "
"devastating event known as <b>the Great Fall</b>, or more simply, <b>the "
"Fall</b>.\n"
"\n"
"Populated by many varied creatures—both sapient and otherwise—Irdya was once "
"a thriving realm that saw the rise and fall of many civilizations, most of "
"them learned in at least one form of magic or technology: humans, elves, "
"dwarves, orcs, to name a few.\n"
"\n"
"Irdya has two suns, named <b>Sela</b> and <b>Naia</b>, as well as one moon "
"occasionally known as <b>Eidyia</b>. Some ancient records of dubious origin "
"claim that a second, smaller moon could seldom be spotted in the times when "
"only Sela roamed the skies.\n"
"\n"
"The largest landmass on Irdya is known as the <b>Great Continent</b>. Much "
"of its geography changed drastically after the Fall, and the current state "
"of civilization has made it impossible to properly chart the alterations."
msgstr ""
"<b>Irdya</b> es el nombre de este vasto mundo. Ha existido desde tiempos "
"inmemoriales y ha pasado por innumerables cambios, el más reciente de los "
"cuales es un evento devastador conocido como <b>la Gran Caída</b>, o más "
"simplemente, <b>la Caída</b>.\n"
"\n"
"Poblado por muchas criaturas variadas —tanto sapientes como no sapientes—, "
"Irdya fue en su momento un reino próspero que vio el ascenso y la caída de "
"muchas civilizaciones, la mayoría expertas en al menos alguna forma de magia "
"o tecnología: humanos, elfos, enanos, orcos, por nombrar algunos.\n"
"\n"
"Irdya tiene dos soles, llamados <b>Sela</b> y <b>Naia</b>, así como una luna "
"a veces conocida como <b>Eidyia</b>. Algunos registros antiguos de dudosa "
"procedencia afirman que una segunda luna más pequeña podía verse raramente "
"en los tiempos en que solo Sela recorría los cielos.\n"
"\n"
"La mayor masa terrestre de Irdya se conoce como el <b>Gran Continente</b>. "
"Gran parte de su geografía cambió drásticamente tras la Caída, y el estado "
"actual de la civilización ha hecho imposible cartografiar adecuadamente las "
"alteraciones."

#. [additional_info]
#: Naia/journey/world.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Irdya is one of ten worlds where a primordial construct known as a <b>Seed</"
"b> was planted; Irdya’s is the <b>Seed of Earth</b>, which during the First "
"Cycle gave way to the dominion of <b>Xia’el</b>, Guardian of Earth."
msgstr ""
"Irdya es uno de los diez mundos donde se plantó una construcción primordial "
"conocida como <b>Semilla</b>; la de Irdya es la <b>Semilla de la Tierra</b>, "
"que durante el Primer Ciclo dio paso al dominio de <b>Xia’el</b>, Guardiana "
"de la Tierra."

#. [world_entry]: id=The_Fall
#: Naia/journey/world.cfg:24
msgid "The Fall"
msgstr "La Caída"

#. [world_entry]: id=The_Fall
#: Naia/journey/world.cfg:25
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"A long time ago, the world of <b>Irdya</b> was completely transformed by a "
"cataclysm referred to as <b>the Great Fall</b>, or more simply, <b>the Fall</"
"b>.\n"
"\n"
"Much of what is currently “known” about the calamity that befell Irdya has "
"been pieced together from fragments passed down through oral tradition by "
"the peoples who survived the turmoil.\n"
"\n"
"It is said that at the exact time of the catastrophe, a deafening boom "
"louder than even the greatest volcanic eruption was heard; the next instant, "
"the earth violently shook and tore asunder, crumbling every bastion of the "
"old empires to dust and sinking even some of the tallest mountains to the "
"depths of the world. Volcanoes everywhere stirred to life and poured molten "
"rock and poisonous ash into the now darkened skies; then, the Vast Ocean "
"rose to meet the clouds before fiercely descending upon the land, claiming "
"what little remained standing after the initial convulsion.\n"
"\n"
"Untold millions perished at the hands of Irdya herself; then in the "
"aftermath, millions more were massacred by the panic-stricken in their "
"senseless frenzy. The impenetrable veil in the sky not only denied all of "
"navigational aid, but also caused all plant life to wither away even in "
"places that had not been directly touched by destruction yet; whether it be "
"from the poisonous rain, or from the accursed darkness that suffocated the "
"earth and submerged all into a timeless haze. Soon, any leaders left or "
"risen amongst the ashes of civilization would resort to barbarism and unholy "
"practices in a desperate attempt to perpetuate their pitiable existences in "
"the warped new world.\n"
"\n"
"Thus, the <b>Golden Age</b> of the peoples of Irdya came to its end.\n"
"\n"
"Many years later, the suns <b>Sela</b> and <b>Naia</b> would finally return, "
"only to turn the once verdant Great Continent into a barren husk of rock and "
"sand; a place where all kinds of life battle each other for survival at day, "
"and vengeful spectres of the past haunt the dunes at night."
msgstr ""
"Hace mucho tiempo, el mundo de <b>Irdya</b> fue completamente transformado "
"por un cataclismo conocido como <b>la Gran Caída</b>, o más simplemente, "
"<b>la Caída</b>.\n"
"\n"
"Mucho de lo que actualmente se “conoce” sobre la calamidad que azotó a Irdya "
"ha sido reconstruido a partir de fragmentos transmitidos por tradición oral "
"por los pueblos que sobrevivieron al caos.\n"
"\n"
"Se dice que en el momento exacto de la catástrofe se escuchó un estruendo "
"ensordecedor más fuerte que la mayor erupción volcánica; al instante "
"siguiente, la tierra tembló violentamente y se desgarró, reduciendo a polvo "
"todos los bastiones de los antiguos imperios y hundiendo incluso algunas de "
"las montañas más altas en las profundidades del mundo. Volcanes de todas "
"partes despertaron y arrojaron roca fundida y ceniza venenosa a los cielos "
"ahora oscurecidos; luego, el vasto océano se elevó para encontrarse con las "
"nubes antes de descender ferozmente sobre la tierra, reclamando lo poco que "
"quedaba en pie tras la convulsión inicial.\n"
"\n"
"Millones incontables perecieron a manos de la propia Irdya; luego, en las "
"secuelas, millones más fueron masacrados por los presa del pánico en su "
"frenesí sin sentido. El velo impenetrable en el cielo no solo negó toda "
"ayuda a la navegación, sino que también hizo que toda vida vegetal se "
"marchitara incluso en lugares que aún no habían sido tocados directamente "
"por la destrucción; ya fuera por la lluvia venenosa o por la oscuridad "
"maldita que asfixiaba la tierra y sumergía todo en una neblina intemporal. "
"Pronto, cualquier líder que quedara o surgiera entre las cenizas de la "
"civilización recurriría al barbarismo y prácticas impías en un intento "
"desesperado por perpetuar sus míseras existencias en el mundo deformado.\n"
"\n"
"Así terminó la <b>Era Dorada</b> de los pueblos de Irdya.\n"
"\n"
"Muchos años después, los soles <b>Sela</b> y <b>Naia</b> finalmente "
"regresarían, solo para convertir al otrora verde Gran Continente en una "
"cáscara árida de roca y arena; un lugar donde todo tipo de vida lucha entre "
"sí por sobrevivir durante el día, y espectros vengativos del pasado acechan "
"las dunas por la noche."

